@startuml fig-text-proto-tcp-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Text Protocol over TCP — Message Exchange with Length Framing

participant "Client\n(TCP)" as C #FFE0B2
participant "Server\n127.0.0.1:3333" as S #C8E6C9

C -> S : TCP connect
note right of S: Thread spawned for client

== Request/Response Cycle ==

C -> S : "20 add user1 Alice"
note right of S
  Parse: LEN=20, cmd=add
  key=user1, resource=Alice
  state.add("user1", "Alice")
end note
S --> C : "13 user1 added"

C -> S : "14 get user1"
S --> C : "8 Alice"

C -> S : "17 remove user1"
S --> C : "15 user1 removed"

C -> S : "7 count"
S --> C : "8 0 keys"

== Unrecognised Command ==

C -> S : "16 foo something"
S --> C : "25 ERR unknown command"

== Termination ==

C -> S : "6 exit"
note over C: Client closes socket

legend right
  Framing: "<LEN> <payload>" where LEN is the
  total character count of the entire message.
  The server reads LEN, then receives exactly
  that many characters before parsing.
  The protocol is stateless per request.
endlegend
@enduml
